{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1047,"text":"Zika fever:"},{"time":4120,"text":"our newest dread disease."},{"time":7850,"text":"What is it? Where'd it come from?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":10870,"text":"What do we do about it?"},{"time":13030,"text":"Well for most adults,\nit's a relatively mild disease --"},{"time":16324,"text":"a little fever, a little headache,\njoint pain, maybe a rash."},{"time":21010,"text":"In fact, most people who get it\ndon't even know they've had it."},{"time":24820,"text":"But the more we find out\nabout the Zika virus"},{"time":28558,"text":"the more terrifying it becomes."},{"time":30130,"text":"For example, doctors\nhave noticed an uptick"},{"time":33661,"text":"of something called Guillain-Barré\nsyndrome in recent outbreaks."},{"time":37399,"text":"In Guillain-Barré, your immune system\nattacks your nerve cells"},{"time":40575,"text":"it can partially\nor even totally paralyze you."},{"time":44272,"text":"Fortunately, that's quite rare,\nand most people recover."},{"time":48220,"text":"But if you're pregnant\nwhen you're infected"},{"time":53900,"text":"you're at risk of something terrible."},{"time":56704,"text":"Indeed, a child with a deformed head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60680,"text":"Here's a normal baby."},{"time":63314,"text":"Here's that infant\nwith what's called microcephaly."},{"time":67075,"text":"a brain in a head that's too small."},{"time":70393,"text":"And there's no known cure."},{"time":73121,"text":"It was actually doctors\nin northeastern Brazil"},{"time":78875,"text":"who first noticed, just a year ago,\nafter a Zika outbreak,"},{"time":84009,"text":"that there was a peak\nin the incidence of microcephaly."},{"time":88763,"text":"It took medical doctors another year"},{"time":90510,"text":"to be sure that it was caused\nby the Zika virus,"},{"time":93326,"text":"but they're now sure."},{"time":94501,"text":"And if you're a \"bring on\nthe evidence\" type,"},{"time":97207,"text":"check out this publication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99760,"text":"So where did it come from,\nand how did it get here?"},{"time":102728,"text":"And it is here."},{"time":104061,"text":"Like many of our viruses,\nit came out of Africa,"},{"time":107441,"text":"specifically the Zika forest in Uganda."},{"time":111776,"text":"Researchers at the nearby\nYellow Fever Research Institute"},{"time":116578,"text":"identified an unknown virus\nin a monkey in the Zika forest"},{"time":120888,"text":"which is how it got its name."},{"time":123593,"text":"The first human cases of Zika fever"},{"time":125830,"text":"surfaced a few years later\nin Uganda-Tanzania."},{"time":129479,"text":"The virus then spread through West Africa"},{"time":133216,"text":"and east through equatorial Asia --\nPakistan, India, Malaysia, Indonesia."},{"time":140344,"text":"But it was still mostly in monkeys\nand, of course, mosquitoes."},{"time":145872,"text":"In fact in the 60 years between the time\nit was first identified in 1947 and 2007"},{"time":151694,"text":"there were only 13 reported cases\nof human Zika fever."},{"time":155731,"text":"And then something extraordinary happened\non the tiny Micronesian Yap islands."},{"time":161700,"text":"There was an outbreak that affected\nfully 75 percent of the population."},{"time":167866,"text":"How did it get there? By air."},{"time":171580,"text":"Today we have two billion\ncommercial airline passengers."},{"time":175340,"text":"An infected passenger can board a plane,\nfly halfway around the world"},{"time":179607,"text":"before developing symptoms --\nif they develop symptoms at all."},{"time":184140,"text":"Then when they land, the local mosquitoes\nbegin to bite them and spread the fever."},{"time":189117,"text":"Zika fever then next surfaced\nin 2013 in French Polynesia."},{"time":195360,"text":"By December of that year, it was being\ntransmitted locally by the mosquitoes."},{"time":201014,"text":"That led to an explosive outbreak in which\nalmost 30,000 people were affected."},{"time":206371,"text":"From there it radiated around the Pacific."},{"time":208792,"text":"There were outbreaks in the Cook\nIslands, in New Caledonia,"},{"time":213704,"text":"in Vanuatu, in the Solomon Islands"},{"time":216148,"text":"and almost all the way around to the coast\nof South America and Easter Island."},{"time":221060,"text":"And then, in early 2015,"},{"time":224536,"text":"there was an upsurge of cases\nof a dengue-like syndrome"},{"time":229393,"text":"in the city of Natal\nin northeastern Brazil."},{"time":233321,"text":"The virus wasn't dengue, it was Zika,\nand it spread rapidly --"},{"time":239447,"text":"Recife down the coast, a big metropolitan\ncenter, soon became the epicenter."},{"time":245415,"text":"Well people have speculated that it was\n2014 World Cup soccer fans"},{"time":251041,"text":"that brought the virus into the country."},{"time":253840,"text":"But others have speculated that perhaps\nit was Pacific Islanders"},{"time":257935,"text":"participating in championship canoe races"},{"time":260618,"text":"that were held in Rio that year\nthat brought it in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263830,"text":"Well today, this is only a year later."},{"time":267763,"text":"The virus is being locally transmitted\nby mosquitoes"},{"time":271204,"text":"virtually throughout South America,\nCentral America, Mexico"},{"time":274489,"text":"and the Caribbean Islands"},{"time":276680,"text":"Until this year, the many\nthousands of cases"},{"time":280091,"text":"that have been diagnosed in the US\nwere contracted elsewhere."},{"time":285076,"text":"But as of this summer, it's being\ntransmitted locally in Miami."},{"time":290258,"text":"It's here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291523,"text":"So what do we do about it?"},{"time":293170,"text":"Well, preventing infection"},{"time":298035,"text":"is either about protecting people\nor about eliminating the mosquitoes."},{"time":302260,"text":"Let's focus on people first."},{"time":304690,"text":"You can get vaccinated."},{"time":307072,"text":"You can not travel to Zika areas."},{"time":311069,"text":"Or you can cover up\nand apply insect repellent."},{"time":314838,"text":"Getting vaccinated is not an option,\nbecause there isn't a vaccine yet"},{"time":318267,"text":"and there probably won't be\nfor a couple of years."},{"time":321853,"text":"Staying home isn't\na foolproof protection either"},{"time":325820,"text":"because we now know that\nit can be sexually transmitted."},{"time":330180,"text":"Covering up and applying\ninsect repellent does work ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333656,"text":"until you forget."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335822,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":337624,"text":"So that leaves the mosquitoes,\nand here's how we control them now:"},{"time":341235,"text":"spraying insecticides."},{"time":344314,"text":"The protective gear is necessary\nbecause these are toxic chemicals"},{"time":348204,"text":"that kill people as well as bugs."},{"time":350829,"text":"Although it does take quite a lot more\nto kill a person than to kill a bug."},{"time":354620,"text":"These are pictures from\nBrazil and Nicaragua."},{"time":358820,"text":"But it looks the same in Miami, Florida."},{"time":361770,"text":"And we of course can spray\ninsecticides from planes."},{"time":367460,"text":"Last summer, mosquito control officials\nin Dorchester County, South Carolina,"},{"time":373698,"text":"authorized spraying of Naled,\nan insecticide,"},{"time":377627,"text":"early one morning,\nas recommended by the manufacturer."},{"time":380990,"text":"Later that day, a beekeeper told reporters"},{"time":385229,"text":"that her bee yard looked\nlike it had been nuked."},{"time":389824,"text":"Oops."},{"time":391879,"text":"Bees are the good guys."},{"time":393640,"text":"The citizens of Florida protested,\nbut spraying continued."},{"time":401251,"text":"Unfortunately, so did the increase\nin the number of Zika fever cases."},{"time":406200,"text":"That's because insecticides\naren't very effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410390,"text":"So are there any approaches that are\nperhaps more effective than spraying"},{"time":418560,"text":"but with less downsides\nthan toxic chemicals?"},{"time":424330,"text":"I'm a huge fan of biological controls,"},{"time":427845,"text":"and I share that view with Rachel Carson,\nauthor of \"Silent Spring,\""},{"time":432362,"text":"the book that is credited with starting\nthe environmental movement."},{"time":437400,"text":"In this book she tells the story,\nas an example,"},{"time":440980,"text":"of how a very nasty insect\npest of livestock"},{"time":446662,"text":"was eliminated in the last century."},{"time":450150,"text":"No one knows that\nextraordinary story today."},{"time":452626,"text":"So Jack Block and I,\nwhen we were writing an editorial"},{"time":456889,"text":"about the mosquito problem today,\nretold that story."},{"time":460127,"text":"And in capsule form, it's that pupae --\nthat's the immature form of the insect --"},{"time":464817,"text":"were irradiated until they were sterile,\ngrown to adulthood"},{"time":469620,"text":"and then released from planes\nall over the Southwest,"},{"time":473254,"text":"the Southeast and down into Mexico\nand into Central America"},{"time":477691,"text":"literally by the hundreds of millions\nfrom little airplanes,"},{"time":481809,"text":"eventually eliminating\nthat terrible insect pest"},{"time":486682,"text":"for most of the Western Hemisphere."},{"time":490175,"text":"Our real purpose in writing this editorial"},{"time":492603,"text":"was to introduce readers\nto how we can do that today --"},{"time":495999,"text":"not with radiation\nbut with our knowledge of genetics."},{"time":500078,"text":"Let me explain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501910,"text":"This is the bad guy: Aedes aegypti."},{"time":504410,"text":"It's the most common insect\nvector of diseases,"},{"time":509095,"text":"not just Zika but dengue,\nChikungunya, West Nile virus"},{"time":512913,"text":"and that ancient plague, yellow fever."},{"time":516970,"text":"It's an urban mosquito,"},{"time":518859,"text":"and it's the female\nthat does the dirty work."},{"time":522789,"text":"She bites to get a blood meal\nto feed her offspring."},{"time":528250,"text":"Males don't bite; they don't even\nhave the mouth parts to bite."},{"time":532599,"text":"A little British company called Oxitec\ngenetically modified that mosquito"},{"time":538781,"text":"so that when it mates with a wild female,\nits eggs don't develop to adulthood."},{"time":545150,"text":"Let me show you."},{"time":546657,"text":"This is the normal reproductive cycle."},{"time":549895,"text":"Oxitec designed the mosquito so that\nwhen the male mates with the wild female"},{"time":555077,"text":"the eggs don't develop."},{"time":556780,"text":"Sounds impossible?"},{"time":558740,"text":"Well let me show you\njust diagrammatically how they do it."},{"time":562540,"text":"Now this represents the nucleus\nof a mosquito cell,"},{"time":566016,"text":"and that tangle in the middle\nrepresents its genome,"},{"time":568992,"text":"the sum total of its genes."},{"time":571516,"text":"Scientists added a single gene"},{"time":574889,"text":"that codes for a protein represented\nby this orange ball"},{"time":579222,"text":"that feeds back on itself\nto keep cranking out more of that protein."},{"time":585240,"text":"The extra copies, however,\ngo and gum up the mosquitoes' genes,"},{"time":590017,"text":"killing the organism."},{"time":592240,"text":"To keep it alive in the laboratory\nthey use a compound called tetracycline."},{"time":596636,"text":"Tetracycline shuts off that gene\nand allows normal development."},{"time":602024,"text":"They added another little wrinkle\nso that they could study what happens."},{"time":606381,"text":"And that is they added a gene\nthat makes the insect glow under UV light"},{"time":613636,"text":"so that when they released it\nthey could follow exactly how far it went"},{"time":617002,"text":"how long it lived\nand all of the kinds of data"},{"time":620780,"text":"for a good scientific study."},{"time":623150,"text":"Now this is the pupal stage,\nand at this stage"},{"time":627286,"text":"the females are larger than the males."},{"time":630600,"text":"That allows them to sort them\ninto the males and the females"},{"time":634492,"text":"and they allow only the males\nto grow to adulthood."},{"time":639238,"text":"And let me remind you\nthat males don't bite."},{"time":641580,"text":"From there it's pretty simple."},{"time":643200,"text":"They take beakers full of male mosquitoes,"},{"time":646826,"text":"load them into milk cartons,\nand drive around the city,"},{"time":649430,"text":"releasing them guided by GPS."},{"time":652858,"text":"Here's the mayor of a city\nreleasing the first batch"},{"time":655399,"text":"of what they call the \"friendly Aedes.\""},{"time":658410,"text":"Now I wish I could tell you\nthis is an American city, but it's not."},{"time":661695,"text":"It's Piracicaba, Brazil."},{"time":664171,"text":"The amazing thing is that in just a year"},{"time":668988,"text":"it brought down the cases\nof dengue by 91 percent."},{"time":674490,"text":"That's better than any insecticide\nspraying can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678420,"text":"So why aren't we using this remarkable\nbiological control in the US?"},{"time":683950,"text":"That's because it's a GMO:\na genetically modified organism."},{"time":690900,"text":"Notice the subtitle here says\nif the FDA would let them"},{"time":695844,"text":"they could do the same thing here,\nwhen Zika arrives."},{"time":698570,"text":"And of course it has arrived."},{"time":700608,"text":"So now I have to tell you the short form"},{"time":704340,"text":"of the long, torturous story\nof GM regulation in the US"},{"time":710927,"text":"In the US, there are three agencies that\nregulate genetically modified organisms:"},{"time":718165,"text":"the FDA, the Food and Drug Administration,"},{"time":720680,"text":"the EPA, the Environmental\nProtection Agency,"},{"time":722926,"text":"and the USDA, US Department\nof Agriculture."},{"time":726520,"text":"Took these folks two years\nto decide that it would be the FDA"},{"time":731337,"text":"that would regulate the genetically\nmodified mosquito."},{"time":734264,"text":"And they would do it as a new animal drug,\nif that makes any sense."},{"time":741310,"text":"Took them another five years going back\nand forth and back and forth"},{"time":744865,"text":"to convince the FDA\nthat this would not harm people,"},{"time":750276,"text":"and it would not harm the environment."},{"time":753280,"text":"They finally gave them, this summer,\npermission to run a little test"},{"time":758631,"text":"in the Florida Keys,"},{"time":760194,"text":"where they had been invited years earlier\nwhen they Keys had an outbreak of dengue."},{"time":767784,"text":"Would that it were that easy."},{"time":770350,"text":"When the local residents heard"},{"time":772580,"text":"that there would be genetically modified\nmosquitoes tested in their community"},{"time":776699,"text":"some of them began to organize protests."},{"time":779548,"text":"They even organized a petition on\nthe internet with this cuddly logo,"},{"time":785143,"text":"which eventually accumulated\nsome 160,000 signatures"},{"time":791404,"text":"And they demanded a referendum"},{"time":793110,"text":"which will be conducted\nin just a couple of weeks"},{"time":796006,"text":"about whether the trials\nwould be permitted at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800315,"text":"Well it's Miami that really needs\nthese better ways of controlling insects."},{"time":806736,"text":"And there the attitudes are changing."},{"time":808901,"text":"In fact, very recently a bipartisan group\nof more than 60 legislators"},{"time":814940,"text":"wrote to HHS Secretary Sylvia Burwell"},{"time":818146,"text":"asking that she, at the Federal level,\nexpedite access for Florida"},{"time":823514,"text":"to this new technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826200,"text":"So the bottom line is this:"},{"time":827811,"text":"biological control of harmful insects"},{"time":831763,"text":"can be both more effective and\nvery much more environmentally friendly"},{"time":836699,"text":"than using insecticides,\nwhich are toxic chemicals."},{"time":841516,"text":"That was true in Rachel Carson's\ntime; it's true today."},{"time":844980,"text":"What's different is that we have\nenormously more information"},{"time":850718,"text":"about genetics than we had then,"},{"time":852639,"text":"and therefore more ability\nto use that information"},{"time":857179,"text":"to affect these biological controls."},{"time":860440,"text":"And I hope that what I've done\nis aroused your curiosity enough"},{"time":865392,"text":"to start your own inquiry --\nnot into just GM mosquitoes"},{"time":870700,"text":"but to the other genetically modified\norganisms that are so controversial today."},{"time":877747,"text":"I think if you do that, and you dig down\nthrough all of the misinformation,"},{"time":882468,"text":"and the marketing"},{"time":883802,"text":"on the part of the organic food industry\nand the Greenpeaces"},{"time":887214,"text":"and find the science,\nthe accurate science,"},{"time":890388,"text":"you'll be surprised and pleased."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893120,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894294,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}